section.p:
Du lait, de l’herbe fraîche –that’s all a Parisian bourgeois has of the ideally idyllic; therein, as everybody knows, lies his view of “
la nature et la vérité! ”
[46] {10}

“
				Tout autre… ”
				[63] I began, paraphrasing Corneille.{14}

“
				Eh bien, mon outchitel, je t’attends, si tu veux ;
				[69] I’m leaving in a quarter of an hour!” she called after me.

“No, lies, lies; and what do you think, that I’m angry? I spit on it; 
				il faut que jeunesse se passe .
				[79] You can’t chase him away, if he was there before me and you love him. Only don’t give him any money, you hear?”
